{
  "text": "The FT-IR spectra of SP1 and SP2 were shown in Fig.  4 . The assignments of FT-IR spectra on SP1 and SP2 are shown in Table 4 and were made according to the literature [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The data revealed the presence of characteristic bands of SP in red seaweeds; the very intense and broad IR bands at 1219 and 1211 cm \u22121 were assigned to asymmetric O=S=O stretching vibration of sulfate esters with some contribution from vibration of COH, CC and CO. The intensity of these bands is proportional to the degree of sulfation [CITATION_4] ). Additionally the medium ",
